prime_award_base_transaction_description: IGF::OT::IGF LOCKHEED MARTIN CHIPS PHASE 1.  THE ASIP TECHNICAL APPROACH IS A THREE-PHASE PROGRAM THAT DEMONSTRATES TWO PRIMARY OBJECTIVES; (1) THE ABILITY OF THE CHIPLET DESIGN APPROACH TO MEET THE CHIPS GOALS OF A MODULAR DESIGN AND FABRICATION FLOW USING OPEN STANDARDS ACHIEVING A LOWER COST, LOWER RISK, SHORTER SCHEDULE , AND LOWER COMPLEXITY SOLUTION TO IC DESIGN, AND (2) THE ABILITY OF THE FUNCTIONAL AND PHYSICAL INTERFACES TO SUPPORT A VARIETY OF SYSTEMS SUBDIVIDED INTO FUNCTIONAL CIRCUIT BLOCKS OR CHIPLETS, SUFFICIENT INTERCONNECT DENSITY IS AVAILABLE, THE INTERCONNECT BANDWIDTHS ARE SCALABLE, THE ENERGY EFFICIENCY SUPPORTS LOW POWER CONNECTIVITY, LATENCIES ARE SUFFICIENTLY LOW, AND OVERALL FLEXIBILITY AND SCALABILITY IS PROVIDED FOR A VARIETY OF APPLICATIONS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: "IGF::CT,CL::IGF" THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS PROCUREMENT IS TO ACQUIRE A SOLUTION THAT WILL PROVIDE THE U.S. GENERAL SERVICES ADMINISTRATION (GSA) HSPD-12 MSO USACCESS PROGRAM UNINTERRUPTED, GOVERNMENT-WIDE CONTRACTOR MANAGED SERVICES FOR IDENTITY AND CREDENTIAL MANAGEMENT SERVICES INCLUDING: 1) APPLICANT SPONSORSHIP, ENROLLMENT , BIOMETRIC SUBMISSION (FOR BACKGROUND INVESTIGATION PURPOSES); 2) CREDENTIAL ISSUANCE, MAINTENANCE (CERTIFICATE REKEY) AND MANAGEMENT AND 3) BIOGRAPHIC&AGENCY SPECIFIC SPONSORSHIP RECORD MAINTENANCE. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE SERVICES THAT MINIMIZE DISRUPTION TO USACCESS CUSTOMER AGENCIES AND SHALL MAINTAIN THE FULL LIFE AND FUNCTIONALITY OF CURRENTLY EXISTING, ISSUED ACTIVE PIV CARDS AND CREDENTIALS.

prime_award_base_transaction_description: THE SCOPE OF DHS TIP IS TO CREATE A PHYSICALLY AND LOGICALLY DIVERSE AND REDUNDANT CAMPUS INFRASTRUCTURE THAT WILL SUPPORT EVERYTHING ON AND WITHIN THE PERIMETER FENCE.   OPEN SYSTEM INTERCONNECTION REFERENCE MODEL (OSI REFERENCE MODEL OR OSI MODEL) LAYER 1 - PHYSICAL LAYER AND LAYER 2 - DATA-LINK LAYER ARE INCLUDED IN THEIR ENTIRETY FOR THE CAMPUS.  ASPECTS OF LAYER 3 - NETWORK LAYER ARE PARTIALLY INCLUDED, AS ARE HIGHER LAYERS FOR ON-SITE SPECIALIZED SYSTEMS (E.G., SECURITY, SMART BUILDINGS APPLICATIONS, AND FIRE SAFETY SYSTEMS.)
